workflow.name: Extract business emails from Google Maps to Google Sheets for lead generation
workflow.description:

This workflow builds a **free lead generation system** that scrapes emails from Google Maps listings and exports them directly into **Google Sheets**. It‚Äôs built in **n8n** using HTTP requests and JavaScript‚Äîno paid APIs required.

Here‚Äôs what it does at a high level:

* üîé Scrapes business listings from Google Maps based on search queries (e.g., ‚ÄúMiami lawyers‚Äù)
* üåê Extracts real business website URLs using regex filtering
* üìß Finds and validates email addresses from each website
* üßπ Cleans data by removing duplicates and invalid entries
* üìä Exports clean email lists into Google Sheets automatically

## Set Up Steps

* Estimated setup time: **1‚Äì2 hours**

  * `searches` ‚Üí add your search queries (e.g., ‚ÄúCalgary dentist‚Äù)
  * `emails` ‚Üí results will be stored here automatically
* Connect Google Sheets credentials in n8n
* Update your Google Sheet document ID in the workflow nodes

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
